# Hostinger reference (JonBeatz)

## Default boundary

JonBeatz is **personal** — do not auto-run MSC `pushit:live`, `msc:hostinger:*`, or Payload deploy unless Jon explicitly requests website deploy **and** MSC workspace is active.

## When Jon mentions Hostinger

1. Read `.cursor/docs/HOSTINGER-REFERENCE.md`
2. Read `.cursor/skills/Hostinger-Ops/SKILL.md`
3. For deploy: execute `.cursor/prompts/Hostinger-MSC.md` (workspace switch + AskQuestion)

## Deploy safety (from MSC production)

1. **Local PC:** build + upload (`pushitup`, `pushit:live*`)
2. **hPanel:** Node.js Restart only
3. **Two-folder model:** FTPS staging → `sync-app` → live root
4. **Avoid MCP zip** on shared Node (`better-sqlite3` compile fails)
5. **Fast deploy:** DB not included by default — use `-WithDb` when CMS data must go live
6. **Partial `.next` uploads** cause vendor-chunks errors — upload full build folder

Full tier reference: `D:\Cursor_Projectz\MyStudioChannel\.cursor\docs\HOSTINGER-DEPLOY.md`

## MCP

`HOSTINGER_API_TOKEN` in JonBeatz `.env.local` → `npm run sync:mcp-env` → global `hostinger-*` servers.

Use scoped launcher `scripts/jonbeatz-hostinger-mcp.mjs` — not default 129-tool `hostinger-api-mcp` binary.

## Pitfalls

See `.cursor/docs/PITFALLS-HOSTINGER.md` before troubleshooting live issues.
